						<summary>

						<p>On a stone set up opposite to a private house.</p>						

						<p>Reḍḍi: Vēmaya-Rācha-Vēma.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 133 • • • • .</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Seems to record a benefacation made by the king. Mentions Sūrāṁba Basadi. Śrīnātha was the composer of the record.</p>						

